.TH "memblock_phys_alloc_try_nid" 9 "memblock_phys_alloc_try_nid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
memblock_phys_alloc_try_nid \- allocate a memory block from specified NUMA node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "phys_addr_t" memblock_phys_alloc_try_nid
.BI "(phys_addr_t size "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t align "  ","
.BI "int nid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
size of memory block to be allocated in bytes
.IP "align" 12
alignment of the region and block's size
.IP "nid" 12
nid of the free area to find, NUMA_NO_NODE for any node
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates memory block from the specified NUMA node. If the node
has no available memory, attempts to allocated from any node in the
system.
.SH "RETURN"
physical address of the allocated memory block on success,
0 on failure.
